-- Taiwan CPC Seeks to Buy High-Sulfur Fuel Oil for April Delivery
-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 2012-02-29T15:41:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/taiwan-cpc-seeks-to-buy-high-sulfur-fuel-oil-for-april-delivery.html
CPC Corp., a Taiwan state-owned oil
company, issued a tender to buy high-sulfur fuel oil for
delivery in April, the company said on its  website .  The company is seeking to buy a cargo loaded with 30,000 to
33,000 metric tons of 180-centistoke fuel oil and 45,000 to
55,000 tons of 380-centistoke grade, according to the statement.
The tender will be awarded on March 2.  To contact the reporter on this story:
